{"title":"How to watch the Tour of Britain 2024 (it’s free)","link":"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-tour-of-britain","date":1724949231000,"content":"<p><a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk\">Cyclist</a><br />\n<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/how-to-watch-tour-of-britain\">How to watch the Tour of Britain 2024 (it’s free)</a></p>\n\n<p>It’s Tour of Britain time again. After a 2023 edition filled with Jumbo-Visma dominance,<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-of-britain-favourites\" target=\"_blank\"> the 2024 race looks set to be a showdown between</a> Olympic stars <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/remco-evenepoel\" target=\"_blank\">Remco Evenepoel </a>and<a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/tags/tom-pidcock\" target=\"_blank\"> Tom Pidcock</a> as well as Julian Alaphilippe, who will race <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/cycling-transfer-rumours\" target=\"_blank\">his final stage race in Quickstep colours</a>. To add to the occasion, the Tour of Britain will be livestreamed globally on YouTube for the first time.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2024 race will roll out of Kelso on Tuesday 3rd September. The race will then head south through North Yorkshire, Sheffield, Northamptonshire and the East Midlands before a final hurrah in Suffolk on Sunday 8th September.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For our British readers, this will be the best time of year to catch some racing in person on the roadsides. However, if you’re not lucky enough to make it onto the six-day-long route, there are plenty of streaming options on YouTube, ITV and Discovery+. There are a number of ways to watch the race for free this year too. I’ll cheers to that!</p>\n\n\n\n\n\n<h2>How to watch the Tour of Britain for free</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Kooij-wins-ToB-Stage-1-by-SWPix-970x647.jpg\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Kooij-wins-ToB-Stage-1-by-SWPix-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Kooij-wins-ToB-Stage-1-by-SWPix-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Kooij-wins-ToB-Stage-1-by-SWPix-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Kooij-wins-ToB-Stage-1-by-SWPix-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Kooij-wins-ToB-Stage-1-by-SWPix-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Kooij-wins-ToB-Stage-1-by-SWPix-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Kooij-wins-ToB-Stage-1-by-SWPix-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Kooij-wins-ToB-Stage-1-by-SWPix-350x233.jpg 350w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/Kooij-wins-ToB-Stage-1-by-SWPix.jpg 1323w\" /><figcaption>Alex Whitehead/SWpix.com</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Tour of Britain’s new organisers British Cycling have confirmed that the race will be broadcast live for free on YouTube. This will be available to watch live and on demand <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/@britishcycling/streams\" target=\"_blank\">via British Cycling’s YouTube channel</a>. This was the case in June for <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/watch-tour-of-britain-women\" target=\"_blank\">the Tour of Britain Women </a>and the British National Road Championships. For the Tour of Britain 2024, there will be no geo-blocking enabled on the YouTube coverage, so it will be free to access across the globe.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>For UK viewers, the Tour of Britain will be broadcast on<a href=\"https://www.itv.com/itvcycling\" target=\"_blank\"> free-to-air channel ITV4</a> too. The stages will be shown live daily from around 11am until 3pm BST. Daily highlights are scheduled each night on ITV4 at 8pm BST. The racing will be streamed via ITV’s streaming site ITVX. This is free to access within the UK (including Northern Ireland). Matt Barbet will anchor the broadcasts with Ned Boulting and David Millar on commentary.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>ITV’s coverage will also be shown live on big screens at each of the finish locations: <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tour-of-britain-route-riders-live-tv-guide-all-you-need-to-know\" target=\"_blank\">Kelso, Redcar, Barnsley, Northampton, Newark and Felixstowe</a>.</p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-of-britain-climbs\">The 5 climbs that will decide the Tour of Britain 2024</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-of-britain-best-moments\">5 standout Tour of Britain moments from the last ten years</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-of-britain-favourites\">Tour of Britain 2024 favourites and riders to watch</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tour-of-britain-route-riders-live-tv-guide-all-you-need-to-know\">Tour of Britain 2024: Route, start list, how to watch and all you need to know</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article></div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <span></span><span></span><span></span>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                        <div>\r\n                                            <div>\r\n                                                <div></div>\r\n                                            </div>\r\n                                        </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                    <div>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                        <span></span>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                    </div>\r\n                                </div>\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\r\n                        </div>\r\n                        </div>\n\n\n<h2>How to watch the Tour of Britain on Discovery+ </h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-003-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"three cyclists followed by a motorbike\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-003-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-003-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-003-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-003-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-003-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-003-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-003-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-003-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-003-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-003-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>James York</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Across Europe, the Tour of Britain will be broadcast live on <a href=\"https://auth.discoveryplus.com/gb/product?flow=purchase&amp;videoAssetId=6021174\" target=\"_blank\">Discovery+</a>. Currently, two hours of racing is scheduled to be broadcast live each day on Discovery+ between 2pm and 4pm BST. The basic package costs £6.99 per month, which includes cycling and all other Eurosport programmes. With so much cycling across the globe in early September, the Tour of Britain will <em>not</em> be broadcast live on Eurosport 1.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Tour of Britain 2024 broadcast times</h2>\n\n\n\n<p><em>All times BST and subject to change by broadcasters</em></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"970\" height=\"647\" src=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-043-970x647.jpg\" alt=\"finish of bike race\" srcset=\"https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-043-970x646.jpg 970w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-043-300x200.jpg 300w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-043-768x512.jpg 768w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-043-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-043-2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-043-750x500.jpg 750w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-043-1140x760.jpg 1140w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-043-465x310.jpg 465w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-043-620x413.jpg 620w, https://dqh479dn9vg99.cloudfront.net/wp-content/uploads/sites/9/2023/09/ToB-2023-Cyclist-Gallery-043-350x233.jpg 350w\" /><figcaption>James York</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>YouTube times TBC.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 1: Kelso to Kelso, Tuesday 3rd September</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>14:00-16:00<br /><strong>ITV4: </strong>10:15-16:15</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 2: Darlington to Redcar, Wednesday 4th September</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>14:00-16:00<br /><strong>ITV4: </strong>10:45-15:15</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 3: Sheffield to Barnsley, Thursday 5th September</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+ </strong>14:00-16:00<br /><strong>ITV4: </strong>10:45-15:45</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 4: Derby to Newark-on-Trent, Friday 6th September</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+: </strong>14:00-16:00<br /><strong>ITV4: </strong>10:45-15:00</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 5: Northampton to Northampton Saturday 8th September</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+  </strong>14:00-16:00<br /><strong>ITV4</strong>: 10:45-15:15</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Stage 6: Lowestoft to Felixstowe, Sunday 9th September</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Discovery+  </strong>14:00-16:00<br /><strong>ITV4</strong>: 10:45-15:30</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>Read our <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/news/tour-of-britain-route-riders-live-tv-guide-all-you-need-to-know\" target=\"_blank\">full Tour of Britain preview</a> including the start list, TV timings and stage profiles.</em></p>\n\n\n<div>\r\n                <div>\r\n                   <div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <h4><span>Related Posts</span></h4>\r\n                      </div>\r\n                      <div>\r\n                         <div>\r\n                            <div>\r\n                            <article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-of-britain-climbs\">The 5 climbs that will decide the Tour of Britain 2024</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-of-britain-best-moments\">5 standout Tour of Britain moments from the last ten years</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                 </article><article>\r\n                    <div>\r\n                       <h4>\r\n                          <a href=\"https://www.cyclist.co.uk/in-depth/tour-of-britain-favourites\">Tour of Britain 2024 favourites and riders to watch</a>\r\n                       </h4>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                